---
const faqs = [
  { n: 'A.01', q: 'What input data do you need?',
    a: "PCF or Isogen export from SmartPlant 3D, AutoCAD Plant 3D, CADWorx, AVEVA E3D. Plus the tracing brief: heating mode, tracer type, temperature profile, coverage rules. No manual data entry, no CAD conversions." },
  { n: 'A.02', q: 'What does "optimal" mean here?',
    a: "Near-optimal in the CARP sense — minimizing total tracer length subject to full coverage and per-circuit capacity constraints. Exact optimum is not computable at industrial scale; Traceopt consistently beats manual routing by 8–12 %." },
  { n: 'A.03', q: 'How does the solver work?',
    a: "Two stages: Reactive Path-Scanning produces a feasible starting solution, then Adaptive Large Neighborhood Search destroys and repairs segments until convergence. Deterministic — same input, same output." },
  { n: 'A.04', q: 'How long does one project take?',
    a: "400–1 000 segments: under 5 minutes of compute, delivered within 1 business day end-to-end. Incremental re-runs on design changes: seconds." },
  { n: 'A.05', q: 'Does this replace our thermal tools?',
    a: "No. Thermal calculation and tracer-type selection stay in your existing tools (Thermon CompuTrace, nVent TraceCalc, in-house calculators). Traceopt solves the routing step alone." },
  { n: 'A.06', q: 'What do we get back?',
    a: "Numbered, separated tracer circuits: routes as (x, y, z) polylines in your coordinate system, circuit BOM (CSV / XLSX), routing report with constraint verification, side-by-side comparison vs manual baseline." },
  { n: 'A.07', q: 'How do we start?',
    a: "Send a brief via the form. The first project is a free pilot — you see the result before any commercial conversation. We sign your NDA template." },
];
---
